Create a Marker Result Function Using HTML

In[]:
def styled_note(text, color="Black", background_color="powderblue", align="center", size="18px"):
    html = f"<div style='text-align:{align}; color:{color}; background-color:{background_color}; font-weight:bold; font-size:{size};'>{text}</div>"
    display(HTML(html))

Create an RFM table to analyze customer purchasing behavior

In[]:
m1 = df.groupby("Customer Name")["Sales"].sum().reset_index() #  m1  Customer Name 

#  m2  Customer Active 
m2 = df.groupby("Customer Name")["Order Date"
      ].apply(lambda x: x.dt.to_period("M")
      .nunique()
      ).reset_index()

behavior_customers = pd.merge(m1, m2, on = "Customer Name") #  m1  m2  Join  Customer Name  behavior_customers
behavior_customers["Monetary"] = behavior_customers["Sales"] / behavior_customers["Order Date"] #    2  Monetary
behavior_customers = behavior_customers[["Customer Name", "Monetary"]] # update  behavior_customers  Customer Name  Monetary

f1 = df.groupby("Customer Name")["Order ID"].nunique().reset_index() #  f1   Order ID  Customer Name 
behavior_customers = pd.merge(behavior_customers, f1, on = "Customer Name") #  f1  3  behavior_customers

r1 = df.groupby("Customer Name")["Order Date"].max().reset_index() #  r1   Customer Name 
r1["lastest_date"] = df["Order Date"].max() #  r1  lastest_date  Transaction
r1["no. date"] = r1["lastest_date"] - r1['Order Date'] #  no. date  Transaction (datetime type)
r1["no. date"] = r1["no. date"].dt.days #  no. date  int
r1 = r1[["Customer Name", "no. date"]] # update  r1  2  Customer Name  no. date

df_rfm1 = pd.merge(behavior_customers, r1, on = "Customer Name") #  r1  behavior_customers  Join  Customer Name  df_rfm1
df_rfm1.columns = ['Customer Name', 'Monetary', 'Frequency', 'Recently (Days)'] #   df_rfm1
df_rfm1 = df_rfm1[["Customer Name", "Recently (Days)", "Frequency", "Monetary"]] #  Customer Name | R | F | M

styled_note(" : ")

Define evaluation criteria for identifying data distribution patterns

In[]:
#   quartile  percentile  3   Recently (Days), Frequency,	Monetary

decisions = {} #  empty dictionary  assign  quartile  percentile

for col in ["Recently (Days)", "Frequency", "Monetary"]: #  for loop  argument 
    skewness = df_rfm1[col].skew() #  df_rfm1 
    if abs(skewness) <= 0.5: #   -0.5  0.5
        decision = "Normal distribution (Quartile is fine)" #   
    elif skewness > 0.5: #   0.5
        decision = "Right-skewed (Percentile is better)" #    percentile
    else:           #   -0.5
        decision = "Left-skewed (Percentile is better)" #    percentile
    decisions[col] = decision #  value  Key  Recently (Days), Frequency, Monetary

styled_note(" : ", decisions)
display(decisions) #  dictionary

Generating RFM Scores for Customer Segmentation

In[]:
df_rfm2 = df_rfm1.copy() # copy table

def assign_rfm_score(value, percentiles, labels): #  assign_rfm_score  parameter 3   percentile
    return labels[np.searchsorted(percentiles, value)] #     percentiles  percentiles  labels 

#  percentile 
recently_percentiles = np.percentile(df_rfm2["Recently (Days)"], [20, 40, 60, 80]) #  percentile  20, 40, 60, 80  Recently (Days)  recently_percentiles
monetary_percentiles = np.percentile(df_rfm2["Monetary"], [20, 40, 60, 80]) #  percentile  20, 40, 60, 80  Monetary  monetary_percentiles

#  RFM  percentile  RM  F 
df_rfm2["R_Score"] = df_rfm2["Recently (Days)" #  R_Score  Score  Recently (Days)
                            ].apply(lambda x: assign_rfm_score(x, recently_percentiles, [5, 4, 3, 2, 1])) #  Recently (Days)   recently_percentiles  5   1 

df_rfm2["F_Score"] = pd.qcut(df_rfm2["Frequency"], q=5, labels=[1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) #  F_Score  5   5  1

df_rfm2["M_Score"] = df_rfm2["Monetary" #  M_Score  Score  Monetary
                            ].apply(lambda x: assign_rfm_score(x, monetary_percentiles, [1, 2, 3, 4, 5])) #  Monetary   recently_percentiles  5   1 

df_rfm2["F_Score"] = df_rfm2["F_Score"].astype(int) #  F_Score  category  int

df_rfm2["Y_(F+M)/2"] = (df_rfm2["F_Score"] + df_rfm2["M_Score"]) / 2 #  F_Score  M_Score 

styled_note(" RFM-Score Columns : ", df_rfm2)
display(df_rfm2) #

Creating the Customer Segment Column Based on RFM Score (RFM Table Final)

In[]:
df_rfm3 = df_rfm2.copy() # reuse Table

def classify_rfm(row): #  2  range  
    r, y = row["R_Score"], row["Y_(F+M)/2"] #  R_Score  Y_(F+M)/2  r  y 

    if r >= 5 and y >= 4:  #  R_Score  5   y  4 
        return "Champions"  #  Champions
    elif r >= 3 and y >= 4:  #  R_Score  3   y  4 
        return "Loyal Customers"  #  Loyal Customers
    elif r >= 4 and 2 <= y < 4:  #  R_Score  4   y  2  4
        return "Potential Loyalists"  #  Potential Loyalists
    elif r >= 5 and 0 <= y < 2:  #  R_Score  5   y  0  2
        return "New Customers"  #  New Customers
    elif 4 <= r < 5 and y < 2:  #  R_Score  4  5  y  2
        return "Promising"  #  Promising
    elif 3 <= r < 4 and 0 <= y < 3:  #  R_Score  3  4  y  3
        return "About to Sleep"  #  About to Sleep
    elif 3 <= r < 4 and 3 <= y < 4:  #  R_Score  3  4  y  3  4
        return "Need Attention"  #  Need Attention
    elif 1 <= r < 3 and y >= 5:  #  R_Score  1  3  y  5 
        return "Can't Lose Them"  #  Can't Lose Them
    elif 1 <= r < 3 and 3 <= y < 5:  #  R_Score  1  3  y  3  5
        return "At Risk"  #  At Risk
    elif 1 <= r < 3 and 2 <= y < 3:  #  R_Score  1  3  y  2  3
        return "Hibernating"  #  Hibernating
    elif 1 <= r < 3 and 0 <= y < 2:  #  R_Score  1  3  y  0  2
        return "Lost"  #  Lost

    else:  #  
        return "Other"  #  Other

#  Segment  DataFrame
df_rfm3["Segment"] = df_rfm3.apply(classify_rfm, axis=1) #   classify_rfm  2  classify_rfm  Segment

 #  segment  Impact 
df_rfm3["Business_Impact"] = np.where(df_rfm3["Segment"] == "Champions", 5, # Champions  5
                  np.where(df_rfm3["Segment"] == "Loyal Customers", 5, # Loyal Customers  5
                  np.where(df_rfm3["Segment"] == "Can't Lose Them", 4, # Can't Lose Them  4
                  np.where(df_rfm3["Segment"] == "Potential Loyalists", 4, # Potential Loyalists  4
                  np.where(df_rfm3["Segment"] == "New Customers", 3, # New Customers  3

%%R

#  Library 
library(tidyverse)
library(lubridate)
library(ggplot2)

#  CSV 

df <- read_csv("sample-store.csv")
colnames(df) <- c("Row_ID", "Order_ID", "Order_Date", "Ship_Date", "Ship_Mode",
                  "Customer_ID", "Customer_Name", "Segment", "Country_Region",
                  "City", "State", "Postal_Code", "Region", "Product_ID",
                  "Category", "Sub_Category", "Product_Name", "Sales",
                  "Quantity", "Discount", "Profit")

#  Date  "%m/%d/%Y"
df <- df %>%
  mutate(
    Order_Date = as.Date(Order_Date, format = "%m/%d/%Y"),
    Ship_Date  = as.Date(Ship_Date, format = "%m/%d/%Y")
  )

#  Monetary:
#   m1 = 
#   m2 =  (unique month)
m1 <- df %>%
  group_by(Customer_Name) %>%
  summarise(total_sales = sum(Sales, na.rm = TRUE))

m2 <- df %>%
  group_by(Customer_Name) %>%
  summarise(unique_months = n_distinct(format(Order_Date, "%Y-%m")))

behavior_customers <- left_join(m1, m2, by = "Customer_Name") %>%
  mutate(Monetary = total_sales / unique_months) %>%
  select(Customer_Name, Monetary)

#  Frequency ( Order_ID )
f1 <- df %>%
  group_by(Customer_Name) %>%
  summarise(Frequency = n_distinct(Order_ID))

behavior_customers <- left_join(behavior_customers, f1, by = "Customer_Name")

#  Recency ()
r1 <- df %>%
  group_by(Customer_Name) %>%
  summarise(last_order_date = max(Order_Date)) %>%
  mutate(latest_date = max(df$Order_Date, na.rm = TRUE),
         recently_days = as.numeric(difftime(latest_date, last_order_date, units = "days"))) %>%
  select(Customer_Name, recently_days)

#  RFM  DataFrame  
df_rfm <- left_join(behavior_customers, r1, by = "Customer_Name") %>%
  select(Customer_Name, recently_days, Frequency, Monetary) %>%
  rename(`Recently (Days)` = recently_days)

#  percentile  Recently  Monetary (20%, 40%, 60%, 80%)
recently_percentiles <- quantile(df_rfm$`Recently (Days)`, probs = c(0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8), na.rm = TRUE)
monetary_percentiles <- quantile(df_rfm$Monetary, probs = c(0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8), na.rm = TRUE)

#  R  M
assign_r_score <- function(x, breaks) {
  #  recency  ()  (5)
  index <- findInterval(x, breaks, rightmost.closed = TRUE)
  return(5 - index)
}

assign_m_score <- function(x, breaks) {
  index <- findInterval(x, breaks, rightmost.closed = TRUE)
  return(index + 1)
}

#  R_Score, F_Score, M_Score  Y_(F+M)/2
df_rfm <- df_rfm %>%
  mutate(
    R_Score = sapply(`Recently (Days)`, assign_r_score, breaks = as.numeric(recently_percentiles)),
    F_Score = ntile(Frequency, 5),  # ntile:  5 
    M_Score = sapply(Monetary, assign_m_score, breaks = as.numeric(monetary_percentiles)),
    `Y_(F+M)/2` = (F_Score + M_Score) / 2
  )

#  Segment  R_Score  Y_(F+M)/2  case_when
df_rfm <- df_rfm %>%
  mutate(
    Segment = case_when(
      R_Score >= 5 & `Y_(F+M)/2` >= 4 ~ "Champions",
      R_Score >= 3 & `Y_(F+M)/2` >= 4 ~ "Loyal Customers",
      R_Score >= 4 & `Y_(F+M)/2` >= 2 & `Y_(F+M)/2` < 4 ~ "Potential Loyalists",
      R_Score >= 5 & `Y_(F+M)/2` >= 0 & `Y_(F+M)/2` < 2 ~ "New Customers",
      R_Score >= 4 & R_Score < 5 & `Y_(F+M)/2` < 2 ~ "Promising",
      R_Score >= 3 & R_Score < 4 & `Y_(F+M)/2` >= 0 & `Y_(F+M)/2` < 3 ~ "About to Sleep",
      R_Score >= 3 & R_Score < 4 & `Y_(F+M)/2` >= 3 & `Y_(F+M)/2` < 4 ~ "Need Attention",
      R_Score >= 1 & R_Score < 3 & `Y_(F+M)/2` >= 5 ~ "Can't Lose Them",
      R_Score >= 1 & R_Score < 3 & `Y_(F+M)/2` >= 3 & `Y_(F+M)/2` < 5 ~ "At Risk",
      R_Score >= 1 & R_Score < 3 & `Y_(F+M)/2` >= 2 & `Y_(F+M)/2` < 3 ~ "Hibernating",
      R_Score >= 1 & R_Score < 3 & `Y_(F+M)/2` >= 0 & `Y_(F+M)/2` < 2 ~ "Lost",
      TRUE ~ "Other"
    )
  )

#  Business_Imact  Segment
df_rfm <- df_rfm %>%
  mutate(
    Business_Imact = case_when(
      Segment %in% c("Champions", "Loyal Customers") ~ 5,
      Segment %in% c("Can't Lose Them", "Potential Loyalists") ~ 4,
      Segment %in% c("New Customers", "Promising") ~ 3,
      Segment %in% c("Need Attention", "About to Sleep", "At Risk") ~ 2,
      Segment %in% c("Hibernating", "Lost") ~ 1,
      TRUE ~ 0
    )
  )

# ---  DataFrame:  Segment ---
segment_n <- df_rfm %>%
  group_by(Segment) %>%
  summarise(`No. Customers` = n()) %>%
  ungroup()

print(segment_n)

#  layout positions (x, y, w, h)  Segment
layout_positions <- tibble(
  Segment = c("Potential Loyalists", "At Risk", "Hibernating", "Loyal Customers",
              "Lost", "Need Attention", "About to Sleep", "Champions",

  x = c(0.50, 0.00, 0.00, 0.33, 0.00, 0.33, 0.33, 0.66, 0.67, 0.50, 0.00),
  y = c(0.16, 0.32, 0.16, 0.48, 0.00, 0.32, 0.00, 0.48, 0.00, 0.00, 0.65),

  h = c(0.32, 0.33, 0.16, 0.33, 0.16, 0.16, 0.32, 0.33, 0.16, 0.16, 0.16)
)

chart_data <- layout_positions %>%
